                            <comment id="18103" author="laisiyao" created="Sat, 23 Jul 2011 09:33:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Peter, I couldn&apos;t reproduce this failure (for 5 days), and to make debug easier, I&apos;d suggest to enable this test on regression to help collect debug logs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18031" author="laisiyao" created="Wed, 20 Jul 2011 20:27:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In maloo test result, one log message are repeated from the beginning of test_124a:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;(ldlm_request.c:1218:ldlm_cli_update_pool()) @@@ Zero SLV or Limit found (SLV: 0, Limit: 102336)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Because zero SLV is invalid, client pool limit and slv won&apos;t be updated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s strange that MDS replies zero SLV to client, because the only chance obd-&amp;gt;obd_pool_slv equals 0 is that ldlm_pool_recalc() is never called. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
